{{see|Table}}

==English==
{{rank|although|knowledge|hath|535|table|daughter|makes|laws}}

===Pronunciation===
*tā'bəl, /ˈteɪbəl/, /"teIb@l/

===Etymology===
From French ''[[table#French|table]]'', from Latin ''[[tabula]]'' ([[tablet]]).

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

#An item of [[furniture]] with a [[flat]] [[top]] [[surface]] raised above the ground on one or more legs.
#A flat [[tray]] which can be used as a table.
#A [[matrix]] or [[grid]] of [[data]] arranged in [[row]]s and [[column]]s.
#A collection of [[arithmetic]] calculations arranged in a table, such as [[multiplication]]s in a [[multiplication table]].
#:''The children were practising multiplication '''tables'''.''
#:''Don’t you know your '''tables'''?''
#: ''Here is a '''table''' of natural logarithms.''
<!-- is this correct? #A proposal.-->
#{{computing}} A [[lookup table]], most often a [[vector]].

